# Database migrations
#
# SQL migration files live here, named with the Supabase convention:
#   <timestamp>_<description>.sql   e.g. 20250101000000_init_identity.sql
#
# Apply locally with `supabase db reset` (re-runs every migration against a
# fresh local database) or push to a linked project with `supabase db push`.
# Per the design, migration groups are applied via the Supabase MCP
# (apply_migration / execute_sql) and types are regenerated afterwards.
